ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class NetworkCapabilitiesChangedEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.NetworkCapabilitiesChangedEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NetworkCapabilitiesChangedEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Not implemented.

    Indicates that a situation occurred during a call's progress in a public or private network that modifies its signalling capability (that is, inter-networking). It does not indicate a change in the connection state of the Network Interface Device (for example, trunk, CO Line) through which the call has accessed the network.

    This event will always be preceded by a NetworkReachedEvent that includes the networkCapability parameter. The event may be repeated according to the situations encountered in the network.

    For an illustration of this event, see ECMA 269, section 17.2.11, Figure 17-43 "Network Capabilities Changed Event".

    This event is caused by the call encountering an interworking situation.

      • getNetworkCapability

        public NetworkCapability getNetworkCapability()
        Returns the value of field 'networkCapability'. The field 'networkCapability' has the following description: Specifies the type of network reached and the Call Control events supported by the network.

        It includes the following components:

        1. networkType (M) - The complete set of possible values is:
          • ISDN public
          • Non-ISDN public
          • ISDN private
          • Non-ISDN private
          • Other
        2. eventsProvided (O) - This is a bitmap of all of the Call Control events defined in this Standard. The call control events are specified in ECMA 269, section 17.2, Table 17-143 "Call Control Events Summary".
        Returns:
        NetworkCapability

      • getProgressIndicator

        public ProgressIndicator getProgressIndicator()
        Returns the value of field 'progressIndicator'. The field 'progressIndicator' has the following description: Specifies an interworking situation encountered in the public or private network outside the switching sub-domain. As a consequence of entering the network, the level of event reporting associated with this call may be reduced.

        This parameter consists of the following components:

        1. progressLocation (M) - It may be one of the following:
          • User
          • Private network serving the local user
          • Public network serving the local user
          • Transit network
          • Public network serving the remote user
          • Private network serving the remote user
          • Local interface controlled by the signalling link
          • International Network
          • Network beyond interworking point
          • Other
        2. progressDescription (M) - It may be one of the following:
          • ISDN Progress Description - This information is derived from ETSI ETS 300 182: 1993.
          • QSIG Progress Description - This information is derived from ECMA-143.
          • Other
        Returns:
        ProgressIndicator
